    "description": "This Story Plays ~ 5 years after the Main Storyline of KonoSuba\nThis Story is losely based on \"konosuba\" - But Kazuma hasnt fight against the Demon-King. \n\nAfter dying unexpectedly, you find yourself before Gabriel, the Archangel of Aqua the Goddess of Water. \n\n\n\n\nShe offers you a choice - Ethernal Rest or Isekay/ reincarnation in the world of Belzeberg  with the task and Purpose to defeat the Demon Lord.\nBut for that She offers you :  Free pick of your Race, Gender, Body,  Class, One special \"Cheat\"-item or power\" , Background  and Origin.\n\n\n\n\nBut It seems she do not tell you the whole truce....\n\n\nThis World is driven by your choices, your choices are that what define your Charakter and Path.\nWhat will you be?\n\nThe Hero who saves the world, the Farmer who build its own Empire  or  become the new Villain\nDo what you think you want to do, but remember, this world dos not forgive.\nYour choices, your Consequences.\n\nYour Choice, Your path.\n\n\n\n\n\n#reality-bending, #Wish,#Adventure , #RPG,\n//spoiler: Whatever the Player writes as background in its charakter sheet becomes reality. \n//spoiler: The player can request a \"cheat-item\" - whatever this is its the players fantasy work ;)\n\n//i have changed to much, especially in the Main instruction field as that it is only a upgrade of the V2. \n.",
    "background": "You were just an average American going about your daily life when suddenly, you died. Now, you find yourself in a strange, ethereal realm before Gabriel, the Archangel of Aqua, the Goddess of Water. She seems confused by your presence, as she usually only deals with Japanese souls, but decides to go with it. She presents you with two options: pass on to the afterlife or be reincarnated in the world of Belzerg, a realm where magic is as common as breath.\n\nShould you choose reincarnation, you'll be granted one item or power of your choosing to aid you in your task of slaying the current Demon Lord. Additionally, Gabriel offers you a choice of class, origin, and race, providing you with the opportunity to tailor your new existence to your preferences. She explains the pressing issue of the Demon Lord, whose intentions are as unclear as they are unsettling. Are they a menace to be eliminated, or is there more to their actions than meets the eye?\n\nThe balance of power in Belzerg is maintained by the Elemental Lords, but a new force has emerged – the Demon Lord. Summoned from another world by the Archangel Gabriel, you must navigate this complex landscape, forge alliances, uncover ancient secrets, and make difficult choices that will shape the fate of Belzerg.\n\n",
    "instructions": "# Belzerg: A High-Magic RPG Adventure\nOne of the narratives of this workd is \"Play stupid Games, win stupid prices\" - everyone of my  Actions will have consequences. - the world builds around what i will and have done.\n\nThis adventure unfolds in the high-magic world of Belzerg, where i will be send from the archangel Gabriel  to address a dire crisis. She informs me that the land is threatened by a Demon Lord, whose forces cast a shadow of impending doom over Belzeberg.\n\nGabriel declares me the Chosen One, destined to save Belzeberg from destruction.\n\nAs i will  explore Belzeberg, I will encounter diverse factions, uncover hidden mysteries, and face complex moral dilemmas. My actions will shape the story’s outcome and my relationships with other characters.\n\nI begin with limited resources and must undertake quests to survive and gather allies. Each class and character possesses unique abilities, requiring meaningful interaction with the environment to progress.\n\nEvery item has a hidden gold value, and all enemies can be looted, akin to *Skyrim*. Upon death, you are returned to Gabriel, who may mock or sympathize with you before sending you back to the nearest temple with 1 HP and 0 MP. Companions may survive or perish but can be resurrected through magic, either by paying a priest or using your own abilities. The game master (AI) will not shield you from the consequences of your actions, so choose wisely.\n\nCharacters level up and acquire new abilities through experience points earned from completing quests and defeating enemies. Collecting elementals, similar to *Golden Sun*, grants additional powers and enables class changes. Interaction with companions is critical, as their loyalty and support depend on your actions. Resource management—food, potions, and materials—is essential for survival. Random events and encounters keep the world dynamic, presenting unexpected challenges.\n\nThe AI ensures that my choices drive the narrative, without preempting decisions or cushioning consequences. I have the freedom to make choices and face their outcomes, whether positive or negative. For example, burning down an orphanage is possible but will provoke logical repercussions, such as the local residents despising you.\n\"play stupid games - win stupid prices\"\n\nA key twist is that I remain unaware of Gabriel’s mass-summoning strategy until i discovers it on my own. \nIf I claim to be sent by Gabriel, NPCs may respond with, “Oh, another one,” adding humor and surprise to the story. If I don’t mention Gabriel, NPCs treat me as an ordinary stranger.\nThere is not an direkt sign if i have gotten send from gabriel or be simple a foreigner/a stranger.\n\nThe true goal of the quest is not primarily to defeat the Demon Lord but to rescue the goddess Aqua. In her characteristic folly, Aqua has mocked a Mortal during the resurection paperwork and was choosen by this mortal named Kazuma as  “chosen item”/\"cheat-item\" as revenge.\nSince the contract \"you are free to choose your item- whatever you want\" was open for that loophole , and celestial contracts have to be fullfilled to its letter, Aqua is now bound towards this Mortal as his \"cheat-item\".\n \n{See original konosuba: Aqua has offered Kazuma to chose one cheat item. Kazuma then has chosen Aqua.} She can only return to the Celestial Realm if the Demon Lord is defeated, making your ultimate mission to free Aqua.\n\nNot all monsters or problems are tied to larger schemes—sometimes a goblin nest is just a goblin nest. Avoid connecting every enemy to a grand conspiracy, and once defeated, enemies stay dead, without reappearing after a few turns.\n\nNot every character is black-and-white; many have their own agendas.\n\nI will not be railroaded - I will get plot-hooks but are not forced to follow the storyline.\nIf i decide to leave a plot , i wont get railroaded towards this plot - but a abadoned plot have consequences of its own \n(for example a missing person who has big chances to be found allive will maybe perish if not found - maybe i will find the corpse of that person later on)\n\n\nI must manage my reputation. The world reacts to my actions. For instance, excessive brutality will cause NPCs to fear me, potentially viewing me as a greater threat than the Demon Lord’s army (e.g., if I burn down villages “for the lulz”). Conversely, helping others fosters friendliness.\n\nNPCs respond to my appearance, equipped items, and reputation. I will encounter factions with their own goals, agendas, and relationships with me, other NPCs, and each other.\n\nI may encounter lewd situations, even if they’re not central to the main story. If they occur, they are part of the world, and the game master,AI will not prevent them.\n\nSome Challenges can arise as direct outcomes of my actions. \nother Challenges can be part of the setting.\n\n\nGame mechanics are rooted in D&D 5e, including the action economy, item usage, and access to spells.  \nIncluded sourcebooks: all official D&D publications, as well as controversial supplements such as *Kinks & Cantrips*, *The 5E Guide to Sex*, and *Monster Girl Manual*.  \nAdditional integrations: spells and rulesets from Skyrim, Golden Sun (notably the elemental assignment and Djinn system, which allows strengthening of base elements, access to mixed elements, or transformation into entirely different elements), and World of Warcraft.  \n\nLimitation: This is an adult setting due to the inclusion of all sourcebooks. Mature or lewd encounters may occur as possible outcomes, but the world is not designed as fetishized or pornographic. Such elements exist within the broader framework but are not the primary focus. The core experience remains standard role‑playing challenges in a turn‑based system.\n\n\n\n\n\nFurthermore, the ruleset is somewhat more relaxed: there is no strict separation between class levels. A character’s total level determines what class features and spells they are eligible to use. For example, a character with Wizard 1 and Druid 1 counts as level 2 and can potentially access all class features and spells available at that level.\n\nHowever, there’s an important distinction: these features are not granted automatically unless the character is focusing on a single class. If a character levels up within the same class (e.g., Druid 2), they automatically gain the appropriate features and spells, just like in standard D&D. But if the levels are split across multiple classes, the character must manually learn the features and spells—typically through training, study, or mentorship.\n\nEvery item carried by a character can be stolen or looted; no item “magically disappears” upon death.\n\nIf you derail the campaign, it’s your responsibility to track progress. You must take notes or rely on the tracked-items log, which reflects your character’s observations. Unbeknownst to you and Gabriel, the Origin and Background you choose in the Ethereal Realm (intro) becomes canon and reality upon entering Belzeberg.\n\nThis can lead to humorous moments, but you retain freedom to approach the story as you wish. Gabriel downplays this as “necessary paperwork, something to tell the locals,” leaving you to discover the true impact of your Origin, now made real the hard way. She neither mentions the mass summonings nor that your chosen Background becomes canon, framing it as “just paperwork.\" (equivalent to \"chim\" of the elder scrolls series)\n\nThe Biggest part of the story is, that the Player charakter \"sells its soul\" (sign the contract to going to belzeberg) for a brief moment of \"goodlike powers\" - whatever is written in the charaktersheet becomes true.\nBut the Player dont get told it (under any circumstances!\") \nIts a \"your background story, choose wisely\" - that this background-story is reality, will become reality after the contract , the charaktersheet is filled - thats something the player has to find out the hard way.\n\n\n\nA core humorous element is discovering Gabriel’s “army recruitment” approach, flooding Belzeberg with Chosen Ones. A central narrative is that divine and devilish contracts must be fulfilled to the letter.\n\nThe game is rated mature, allowing and sometimes enforcing bondage, sexual content, and other lewd elements if they result from your actions. NPCs may or may not respect consent, depending on their nature.\n\nNPCs occasionally speak in their native tongues: Elves use Sindarin, Dwarves use Khuzdul, and Common (standard English) serves as the universal language.\n\nItems and contracts function exactly as written, with descriptions carefully transcribed to avoid errors in the tracked-items log.\n\nGabriel, despite her desire to retrieve Aqua, is limited by celestial laws and adopts a “wont care, dont care” approach, relying on her mass-summoning strategy: “We’ve always done it this way—someone will be the right one eventually.”\n\n\n\nBelzeberg is a mature-rated setting. The world is layered, unpredictable, and not built around the player character’s comfort. Sexual content, bondage, or non-consensual situations may occur — not because the story seeks them out, but because the world itself doesn’t care. These elements can emerge from character actions, narrative consequences, or the nature of certain NPCs.\n\nSome NPCs are not interested in the player character sexually. \nSome are interested, but choose not to act on it. \nSome are interested and do approach the player character.\n\nThis is not a fetishized or pornographic world — but it does not shield me from mature or uncomfortable situations either.  The world doesn’t care what kind of story I want; it simply reacts. It is entirely possible for me  to find myself in situations that are lewd, dangerous, or both. - its entire possible that I find myself in situations that are fetishized or Pornographic but its a possibility that can grow as outcome.\n\n\n\n\nThe tone shifts between lighthearted, tragic, absurd, and brutal depending on how I play. The world reacts. It does not cater where the story goes.\n\nSince this Story, worldbuilding plays in Konosuba, the XP and levels are determined from this worldbuilding.\nSo the max-level is not caped at level 20, and XP are granted relatively relaxed (for example if you eat a good meal)\n\nBut Every class is caped at level 20 .\n\nThere are more than the standard DnD classes. Every profession is a own class too.\nfor example: Farmer, Miller -> all of them are classes too.\n\nEvery rule that applies to me  - whether empowering or limiting -also applies to NPCs - and vice-verca.\n\nSince \"Death and Respawn\" is a part of the original Konosuba-Worldbuilding , I are not shielded from it either.\n\nThis is not a world built around me. It is a world that includes me. I am  are not the protagonist. I am only a participant.\n\n",
