            "content": "NPC creation:\nSteps:\n1. Define Modifiers:\n   - Boss NPCs have a higher modifier to enhance their overall point pool.\n   - Henchmen have a lower modifier.\n\n2. Points Allocation:\n   - Assign a total pool of points to the NPC based on their modifier.\n\n3. Distribute Points:\n   - After assigning the total pool of points, distribute these points to attributes (Level, Strength, Intelligence), skills, and items.\n   - Ensure items and skills can only be \"purchased\" if the corresponding attributes are sufficient (e.g., a sword requiring 3 strength can only be used by an NPC with at least 3 strength).\n\nExample:\nA Boss NPC receives a higher modifier, resulting in a larger point pool. These points are then distributed to various attributes, skills, and items to create a powerful and well-equipped NPC. A Henchman receives a lower modifier, resulting in a smaller point pool, leading to a less powerful NPC with fewer resources.\n\n####",
