            "content": "Class: Summoner (Homebrew Class for D&D 5e)\nSource: https://homebrewery.naturalcrit.com/share/P5bq92SoM\nCopyright: © The original author on Homebrewery. This summary is for reference only and not a replacement for the original work.\n\nClass definition: {\n  Hit Dice: d8\n  Primary Ability: Charisma\n  Saving Throws: Constitution, Charisma\n  Armor Proficiencies: Light armor\n  Weapon Proficiencies: Simple weapons\n  Tools: None\n  Spellcasting: Full caster progression (like Wizard), unique summoner spell list\n\n  Starting Equipment:\n    - A simple weapon\n    - A component pouch or arcane focus\n    - A scholar’s pack or explorer’s pack\n    - Leather armor and a dagger\n\n  Level Progression Table:\n    Levels 1–20:\n      - Spellcasting progression: Full caster (same as Wizard)\n      - Eidolon Companion: Starts at level 1\n      - Evolution Points: Begin at level 2, increase with level\n      - Subclass (Summoner’s Path): Choose at level 3\n      - Ability Score Improvements: Levels 4, 8, 12, 16, 19\n      - Capstone: Merge with Eidolon (level 20)\n\n  Class Features:\n\n  Eidolon Companion:\n    Mechanical:\n      - Summon a magical creature bound to your soul\n      - Shares initiative\n      - Acts on your command\n      - Has its own stat block (scales with level)\n      - Evolves via Evolution Points\n      - Can be dismissed/resummoned\n    Lore:\n      A spiritual projection of your will, shaped by your desires and imagination.\n\n  Summoner’s Bond:\n    Mechanical:\n      - Telepathic link within 100 ft\n      - Share senses (1 min per long rest)\n      - Swap positions (from level 7+)\n    Lore:\n      The bond is more than magical—it’s emotional and metaphysical.\n\n  Spellcasting:\n    Mechanical:\n      - Charisma-based casting\n      - Unique summoner spell list\n      - Ritual casting\n      - Eidolon can be used as spell origin (from level 6+)\n    Lore:\n      Summoners channel the essence of otherworldly beings through their Eidolon.\n\n  Evolution Points:\n    Mechanical:\n      - Gained at level 2 and every few levels thereafter\n      - Spent to grant Eidolon traits (e.g., wings, resistances, attacks)\n      - Evolutions can be changed during long rests\n    Lore:\n      Eidolons are fluid beings, reshaped by the summoner’s will and growth.\n\n  Subclasses (Summoner’s Path):\n    Evolutionist:\n      - Focus on Eidolon customization\n      - Extra Evolution Points\n      - Can mutate Eidolon mid-combat (limited uses)\n\n    Conduit:\n      - Channel spells through Eidolon\n      - Eidolon can store and release spells\n      - Shared casting abilities\n\n    Master of Many:\n      - Summon multiple lesser creatures\n      - Battlefield control\n      - Eidolon becomes a commander of spirits\n\n  Capstone (Level 20):\n    Merge with Eidolon:\n      - Temporarily fuse with Eidolon\n      - Gain its traits and abilities\n      - Enhanced spellcasting and physical power\n\n  Design Philosophy:\n    - Inspired by Pathfinder’s Summoner and Final Fantasy\n    - Emphasizes synergy, customization, and tactical depth\n    - Eidolon is central to identity and power\n}\n\nClass: Summoner\nSource: https://homebrewery.naturalcrit.com/share/P5bq92SoM\nCopyright: © Original author on Homebrewery. This structured summary is for reference only and not a replacement for the original work.\n\nClassDefinition: {\n  HitDice: d8,\n  PrimaryAbility: Charisma,\n  SavingThrows: [Constitution, Charisma],\n  ArmorProficiencies: [Light armor],\n  WeaponProficiencies: [Simple weapons],\n  Tools: [],\n  Spellcasting: {\n    Progression: \"Full caster\",\n    RitualCasting: true,\n    SpellcastingAbility: \"Charisma\",\n    EidolonCasting: true\n  },\n  StartingEquipment: {\n    Weapon: \"Simple weapon\",\n    Focus: \"Component pouch or arcane focus\",\n    Pack: \"Scholar’s pack or explorer’s pack\",\n    Armor: \"Leather armor\",\n    Extra: \"Dagger\"\n  }\n}\n\nLevelProgression: {\n  1: {Features: [\"Ei