    "designNotes": "--- Original user world design prompt: ---\n\n\"Create a captivating fantasy adventure in the Isekai genre. The player is summoned to the world of Eldoria by a goddess who needs help to solve a pressing issue. The player can freely choose their class, origin, and race.\n\nEldoria is currently threatened by a Demon Lord who has decided to conquer the land. The goddess only knows what the prayers from the inhabitants tell her—that the Demon Lord is a menace. She relays this information to the player, but it remains uncertain whether the Demon Lord is truly the main antagonist or if another force, such as the head of the church, might actually be the true threat.\n\nAs the player explores the world, they may discover that the Demon Lord might have a justified reason for his actions, such as protecting the land from human exploitation and environmental destruction. However, it is also possible that the Demon Lord is simply a malevolent force, like \"The Nothing\" from \"The NeverEnding Story\" or the humans in \"Avatar,\" who seeks to achieve his goals by ravaging the land.\n\nThe game world is loosely based on the Isekai manga \"Konosuba\". The ruleset is inspired by tabletop genres like Dungeons & Dragons or Pathfinder, with the additional twist of collecting elementals like in Golden Sun to increase power or even change class.\n\nKey Features:\n\nCharacter Customization: At the beginning, the player can communicate with the goddess to choose their class, origin, and race.\n\nQuests and Challenges: The player starts with limited resources and is forced to take on various quests to survive and gather their party.\n\nDynamic Power System: Each class and character has an extremely powerful \"once a day\" ability that weakens the character after use.\n\nRich World: Eldoria has a detailed background story with kingdoms, cities, and various races, each with their own histories and conflicts.\n\nHigh-Magic Setting: The world features a high-magic setting where powerful spells and magical abilities are common. Technology like artillery is rare and considerably weaker compared to the magical capabilities.\n\nUncertain Antagonist: The true nature of the threat remains uncertain, allowing for intriguing plot twists and moral dilemmas. The player must investigate and determine whether the Demon Lord or another force is the true enemy, discovering that the Demon Lord might have a justified reason for his actions, or he might be a malevolent force.\n\nComplex Relationships: The player will encounter various factions and characters with their own agendas and motivations. Building alliances and navigating political intrigue will be key to success.\n\nMysteries and Secrets: The world of Eldoria is filled with hidden mysteries and ancient secrets. The player will uncover forgotten lore, lost artifacts, and hidden paths that reveal the deeper history of the land.\n\nEnvironmental Interactions: The player can interact with the environment in meaningful ways, such as using magic to manipulate the elements, crafting powerful items, and building structures to aid in their quests.\n\nMoral Choices: Throughout the adventure, the player will face difficult moral choices that will shape the outcome of the story and their relationships with other characters.\n\nLoot and Economy: Every item has a hidden gold value, and every enemy can be looted like in Skyrim, allowing the player to take equipped items from defeated foes.\n\nDeath and Resurrection: If the player dies, they are sent back to the goddess, who either mocks or sympathizes with them before sending them back to the nearest temple with 1 HP and 0 MP. Companions may survive or perish but can be resurrected through magic, either by paying a priest or by the player's own abilities.\n\nConsequences for Actions: The AI will not shield the player from the consequences of their actions. If the player makes poor choices or acts recklessly, they will face the repercussions. For example, burning down an orphanage is possible, but the local residents will despise the player for it. The AI will question questionable decisions, but if the player insists, they must face the outcomes.\"\n\n"
